spec: concurrent_futures_extra51
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(concurrent.futures)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html#concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor — ThreadPoolExecutor documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html#concurrent.futures.Future — Future documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends concurrent_futures_extra50.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor __name__/__module__/__qualname__, CancelledError/TimeoutError/BrokenExecutor/InvalidStateError identity and bases, as_completed/wait __name__/__qualname__, FIRST_COMPLETED/FIRST_EXCEPTION/ALL_COMPLETED values and __len__(), class __module__/__name__/__len__() tables, submit/shutdown qualname lens, Future method qualname lens, class __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() tables (extra28/extra31: lengths only), as_completed/wait __module__.__len__(), __all__.__len__()==14, __mro__.__len__() tables, __bases__[0].__name__.__len__() for all classes, Executor context manager qualname lens, wait sentinel string lengths, class qualname lengths, executor __init__ qualname lengths, map/__qualname__.__len__() for both executors, Future/ThreadPoolExecutor method __name__/__qualname__.__len__() tables, InvalidStateError/__name__.__len__()==17, CancelledError/__qualname__.__len__()==14, BrokenExecutor lengths, CancelledError/__module__.__len__()==24, TimeoutError/__name__/__module__.__len__(), concurrent.futures.__package__.__len__()==18 (extra35), executor __name__ equality, executor __module__ equality, Executor/__name__/__module__ equality, exception identity/MRO depths, class __qualname__ equality tables (extra41), module string equality for thread/process/builtins (extra42), Future/__module__ lengths (extra43), class __class__.__name__=='type'/'function' tables (extra44), class __class__.__qualname__ equality tables (extra45), FIRST_COMPLETED/FIRST_EXCEPTION/ALL_COMPLETED string/class facts (extra46), class __doc__/__class__/__name__/__qualname__/__module__ tables (extra47), ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor qualname string equality (extra48), wait/as_completed __doc__/__class__/__module__/__name__/__qualname__ (extra49), concurrent.futures.__name__/__package__ string equality and InvalidStateError/__module__/__len__() and TimeoutError/__bases__[0]/__qualname__ (extra50). wait.__qualname__.__eq__('wait') (extra49). as_completed.__qualname__.__eq__('as_completed') (extra49)."
    - "This spec covers: concurrent.futures class __dict__.__class__.__name__ string equality ('mappingproxy') for ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor/CancelledError/BrokenExecutor — prior specs (extra28/extra31) captured only __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12; extra51 captures the full string equality in the cfdict51 namespace. Also: ThreadPoolExecutor/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ and Future/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ string equality ('mappingproxy'). Also: concurrent.futures.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — module-level __dict__ is also a mappingproxy. Also: wait/__qualname__.__len__()==4 and as_completed/__qualname__.__len__()==12 cross-checks."
    - "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Every Python class __dict__ is a mappingproxy — a read-only view of the class namespace dictionary. ThreadPoolExecutor is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py; its __dict__ has __class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars). Prior spec extra28 captured __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12; extra51 captures the string equality in the cfdict51 namespace. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. ProcessPoolExecutor is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. Prior extra28 captured __len__()==12; extra51 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Future is the core result object in concurrent.futures, defined in _base.py; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. Prior extra28 captured __len__()==12; extra51 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Executor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Executor is the abstract base class for ThreadPoolExecutor and ProcessPoolExecutor, defined in _base.py; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. Prior extra28 captured __len__()==12; extra51 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.CancelledError.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. CancelledError is an exception class in concurrent.futures; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. No prior spec captured string equality for CancelledError __dict__.__class__.__name__; extra51 introduces this check. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. BrokenExecutor is an exception class in concurrent.futures indicating a broken pool; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. Prior extra28 captured __len__()==12; extra51 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy'. The mappingproxy type is a built-in type with no enclosing class or function scope, so __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'. No prior concurrent.futures spec has captured __dict__.__class__.__qualname__; extra51 opens this dimension. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy'. Same reasoning as ThreadPoolExecutor: mappingproxy is a built-in type with __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Novel __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check for Future. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Module __dict__ objects are also mappingproxy instances in CPython — the module's global namespace is exposed as a mappingproxy via the module's __dict__ attribute. No prior concurrent.futures spec has examined the module-level __dict__.__class__.__name__. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.wait.__qualname__.__len__() == 4. 'wait' has 4 characters. Prior extra49 captured wait.__qualname__.__eq__('wait') (the string equality); extra51 captures the complementary __len__()==4 cross-check in the cfdict51 namespace. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.as_completed.__qualname__.__len__() == 12. 'as_completed' has 12 characters: a-s-_-c-o-m-p-l-e-t-e-d = 12. Prior extra49 captured as_completed.__qualname__.__eq__('as_completed') (the string equality); extra51 captures the complementary __len__()==12 cross-check. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures class __dict__.__class__.__name__ string equality — extra51
#
# Every Python class __dict__ is a mappingproxy, a read-only view of the class
# namespace dictionary. The mappingproxy type has:
#   __class__.__name__     == 'mappingproxy'  (12 chars)
#   __class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy'  (12 chars)
#
# Prior specs (extra28/extra31) measured __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12
# for several concurrent.futures classes but never the 'mappingproxy' string equality.
# Extra51 introduces the string equality checks in the cfdict51 namespace for:
#   ThreadPoolExecutor, ProcessPoolExecutor, Future, Executor, CancelledError,
#   BrokenExecutor
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra51.class_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures class __dict__.__class__.__name__ string equality in extra51 namespace — all class __dict__ objects are mappingproxy instances; prior specs captured __len__()==12 only"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: cfdict51clsname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [ThreadPoolExecutor,  ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["mappingproxy"], true, "ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — class __dict__ is always a mappingproxy in CPython; prior extra28 captured __len__()==12 but not the string equality"]
    - [ProcessPoolExecutor, ProcessPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["mappingproxy"], true, "ProcessPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy"]
    - [Future,              Future.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,              ["mappingproxy"], true, "Future.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy"]
    - [Executor,            Executor.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,            ["mappingproxy"], true, "Executor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — abstract base class defined in _base.py; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy"]
    - [CancelledError,      CancelledError.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,      ["mappingproxy"], true, "CancelledError.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — exception class; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; novel string equality check not in prior specs"]
    - [BrokenExecutor,      BrokenExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,      ["mappingproxy"], true, "BrokenExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — exception class indicating a broken pool; prior extra28 captured __len__()==12, extra51 adds the string equality"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures class __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ string equality — extra51
#
# The mappingproxy type is a built-in type with no enclosing class or function
# scope, so __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'. No prior concurrent.futures
# spec has captured __dict__.__class__.__qualname__. Extra51 covers
# ThreadPoolExecutor and Future as representative cases.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra51.class_dict_class_qualname_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures class __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ string equality in extra51 namespace — mappingproxy has __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: cfdict51clsqualname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [ThreadPoolExecutor, ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__, ["mappingproxy"], true, "ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — mappingproxy is a built-in type with no enclosing scope; __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); novel check not in prior specs"]
    - [Future,             Future.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__,             ["mappingproxy"], true, "Future.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — built-in mappingproxy type; __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'; novel __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check for Future"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures module __dict__.__class__.__name__ — extra51
#
# Module __dict__ objects are also mappingproxy instances in CPython.
# The module's global namespace is exposed as a mappingproxy via __dict__.
# No prior concurrent.futures spec has examined the module-level __dict__.__class__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.module_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — module __dict__ is a mappingproxy in CPython; the module namespace is exposed as a read-only mappingproxy via __dict__; novel module-level check not in prior concurrent.futures specs"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: concurrent.futures.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures wait and as_completed __qualname__.__len__() — extra51
#
# Prior spec extra49 captured the string equality checks:
#   wait.__qualname__.__eq__('wait') == true
#   as_completed.__qualname__.__eq__('as_completed') == true
#
# Extra51 captures the complementary __len__() cross-checks:
#   wait.__qualname__.__len__() == 4    ('wait' = 4 chars)
#   as_completed.__qualname__.__len__() == 12  ('as_completed' = 12 chars)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra51.function_qualname_len:
  description: "concurrent.futures wait and as_completed __qualname__.__len__() cross-check in extra51 namespace — 'wait'==4, 'as_completed'==12"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: module_identity
  id_prefix: cfdict51funcqualnamelen

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [wait,         wait.__qualname__.__len__,         [],  4, "wait.__qualname__.__len__() == 4 — 'wait' has 4 characters; cross-check for wait.__qualname__=='wait' from extra49"]
    - [as_completed, as_completed.__qualname__.__len__, [], 12, "as_completed.__qualname__.__len__() == 12 — 'as_completed' has 12 characters: 'as_completed' = a(1)+s(2)+_(3)+c(4)+o(5)+m(6)+p(7)+l(8)+e(9)+t(10)+e(11)+d(12); cross-check for as_completed.__qualname__=='as_completed' from extra49"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra51
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.ThreadPoolExecutor_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — every Python class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; 'mappingproxy' is 12 chars; prior extra28 captured __len__()==12, extra51 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.ProcessPoolExecutor_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra28 captured __len__()==12, extra51 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ProcessPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.Future_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.Future.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra28 captured __len__()==12, extra51 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Future.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.Executor_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.Executor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — abstract base class; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra28 captured __len__()==12, extra51 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Executor.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.CancelledError_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.CancelledError.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — exception class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; novel string equality check not covered by prior specs"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: CancelledError.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.BrokenExecutor_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — exception class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra28 captured __len__()==12, extra51 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: BrokenExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.ThreadPoolExecutor_dict_class_qualname_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — mappingproxy is a built-in type with no enclosing scope; __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); first __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check in concurrent.futures specs"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ThreadPoolExecutor.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.Future_dict_class_qualname_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.Future.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — mappingproxy is a built-in type; __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'; novel __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check for Future"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Future.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.wait_qualname_len:
  description: "concurrent.futures.wait.__qualname__.__len__() == 4 — 'wait' has 4 characters; cross-check for wait.__qualname__=='wait' from extra49; wait is a module-level function with __qualname__ == __name__ == 'wait'"
  category: module_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: wait.__qualname__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 4

invariant concurrent_futures_extra51.as_completed_qualname_len:
  description: "concurrent.futures.as_completed.__qualname__.__len__() == 12 — 'as_completed' has 12 characters: 'as_'(3)+'completed'(9) = 12; cross-check for as_completed.__qualname__=='as_completed' from extra49"
  category: module_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: as_completed.__qualname__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 12
